to add the MySQL Connector JAR in IntelliJ:
ðŸ”¹ Option 1: Add JAR Manually (Non-Maven/Gradle Project)

If your project is a plain Java project (no Maven/Gradle):
1. Download MySQL Connector JAR
   - Go to: [MySQL Connector/J download page](https://dev.mysql.com/downloads/connector/j/)
   - Download `mysql-connector-java-8.x.x.jar`.

2. Copy JAR into Project:
   - Place the JAR inside your project folder (e.g., create a `lib/` folder inside your project).

3. Add to IntelliJ Project Structure:
   - Open IntelliJ â†’ `File` â†’ `Project Structure` (or press `Ctrl+Alt+Shift+S`).
   - Go to Modules â†’ Dependencies tab.
   - Click + â†’ JARs or Directories.
   - Select your `mysql-connector-java-8.x.x.jar`.
   - Apply and OK.
4. Run your project again.**
   IntelliJ should now find the driver class `com.mysql.cj.jdbc.Driver`.


ðŸ”¹ Option 2: Use Maven (Recommended)
If you are using Maven, you donâ€™t need to download manually. Just add this dependency in `pom.xml`:
```xml
<dependency>
    <groupId>mysql</groupId>
    <artifactId>mysql-connector-java</artifactId>
    <version>8.0.33</version>
</dependency>
```

Then right-click on your project â†’ Maven â†’ Reload Project.
Maven will automatically download the JAR and add it to your classpath.

ðŸ”¹ Option 3: Use Gradle: If youâ€™re on Gradle, add this in `build.gradle`:

```gradle
dependencies {
    implementation 'mysql:mysql-connector-java:8.0.33'
}
```
Then do a Gradle refresh.